The Address Homes Limited, a real estate development firm has announced the addition of two new housing brand schemes. According to the firm, the two schemes are called ‘Luxuria’ and ‘Dan & Dan’ and are expected to deliver homes that combine high-class contemporary architectural design with high-level finishes within Ikoyi. In a statement, the company announced that the construction of the homes is expected to be completed in 2023. The Chairman and founder, The Address Homes, Dr Bisi Onasanya, said, “In creating these luxury homes, we took into consideration the need for space optimization, comfort, security, child-friendly environment, and quality of materials. “At The Address Homes, we build homes with clients at the core and heart of our processes.”  Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com